# {{{ = Window Rules =========================================================
# SWAY: criteria matching is an unanchored SUBSTRING search, not a whole-
#       string match (confirmed via `sway(5)` CRITERIA section + live testing).
#       Use ^/$ or a (^|[ ._-])...([ ._-]|$) boundary group to avoid
#       accidental matches on short/generic tokens.
# SWAY: \b (word boundary) is silently broken in for_window/config-parsed
#       criteria -- verified live that it gets eaten (likely stripped as an
#       unrecognized backslash-escape by the config string parser), so
#       for_window rules using it never match, while the *identical* pattern
#       works fine via an ad-hoc runtime `swaymsg '[...] ...'` command (which
#       doesn't go through config parsing). Use the (^|[ ._-])...([ ._-]|$)
#       character-class form in for_window/no_focus instead; reserve \b for
#       one-off runtime swaymsg calls (e.g. bin/sway-app, which matches via
#       jq, not sway's own criteria parser, and is unaffected by this).
# SWAY: [class=...] matches XWayland apps; [app_id=...] matches Wayland-native
#       apps. Both are kept here for broad compatibility, where verified.
# SWAY: no native way to OR across attribute keys (app_id vs class) in one
#       rule -- all given keys are ANDed, and $variables don't substitute
#       inside [...] criteria values (tested). One rule per attribute is the
#       only option; regex alternation (|) still works within one value.

